up zsh and nvm. If you haven't, finish those first or you'll likely hit weird issues:",[35,36,37,47],"ul",{},[38,39,40],"li",{},[41,42,46],"a",{"href":43,"rel":44},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fother\u002F20200123\u002F1105303313\u002F",[45],"nofollow","Mac OS terminal beautification, all in one post (article in Mandarin)",[38,48,49],{},[41,50,52],{"href":51},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2020\u002F01\u002F24\u002Finstall-nvm-on-mac-os-x\u002F","Installing nvm on Mac OS X",[12,54,55],{},"If you've got nvm installed and zsh (oh-my-zsh) configured, you're good to continue.",[20,57,59],{"id":58},"installing-zsh-nvm","Installing zsh-nvm",[12,61,62,63,67,68,71,72,75,76,79,80,83],{},"As I mentioned, each project uses a different Node.js version, and your ",[64,65,66],"code",{},"nvm"," default might also differ. For example, your project needs ",[64,69,70],{},"18.17.0"," but nvm defaults to ",[64,73,74],{},"16.15.0"," — easy to forget ",[64,77,78],{},"nvm use 18.17.0",". ",[64,81,82],{},"zsh-nvm"," handles the switching for us.",[12,85,86,87,91],{},"The ",[41,88,82],{"href":89,"rel":90},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Flukechilds\u002Fzsh-nvm",[45]," docs list multiple install methods:",[35,93,94,97,100,103,106],{},[38,95,96],{},"antigen",[38,98,99],{},"zplug",[38,101,102],{},"zgen",[38,104,105],{},"manual",[38,107,108],{},"as an oh-my-zsh custom plugin",[12,110,111],{},"I'll go with \"As an Oh My ZSH! custom plugin\" since I'm using oh-my-zsh.",[12,113,114],{},"In the terminal, install zsh-nvm into oh-my-zsh's custom plugins folder:",[116,117,122],"pre",{"className":118,"code":119,"language":120,"meta":121,"style":121},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","git clone https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Flukechilds\u002Fzsh-nvm ~\u002F.oh-my-zsh\u002Fcustom\u002Fplugins\u002Fzsh-nvm\n","bash","",[64,123,124],{"__ignoreMap":121},[125,126,129,133,137,140],"span",{"class":127,"line":128},"line",1,[125,130,132],{"class":131},"s_sBn","git",[125,13